article.headline: SMU 57, Prairie View 49
article.story: DALLAS (AP) -- Derrick Roberts scored 15 points for Southern Methodist, which hit 24 of 36 free throws in the second half to beat Prairie View A&M 57-49 on Thursday night. Bamba Fall came off the bench to score 12 points and pull down nine rebounds for the Mustangs (5-5), which came from behind. Prairie View (2-8) was led by Brian Ezeh's 11 points and 10 rebounds, both highs for the Panthers. Prairie View led 33-27 early in the second half when SMU began coming back. SMU led the rest of the way after Roberts hit a 3-pointer for a 36-33 lead. The Mustangs hit 30 of 45 free throws for the game, and the Panthers' Blake Thompson and Jonathan Dixon both fouled out. Both teams were cold shooting from the field, with Prairie View shooting 31 percent and SMU 32 percent for the game.
